Debra A. Sandler: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 1:50 PM ET
Food Products

Company Overview of Mars, Incorporated



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Debra A. Sandler  Chief Health and Wellbeing Officer, Mars, IncorporatedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Ms. Debra A. Sandler serves as Worldwide President of McNeil Nutritionals, LLC. Ms. Sandler founded LaGrenade Group, LLC and also has been its President since October, 2015. She has strong marketing and operating experience and a proven record of creating, building, enhancing and leading well-known consumer brands as a result of the leadership positions, she has held with Mars, Johnson & Johnson and PepsiCo. She served as the President of Chocolate for North America ... of Mars, Inc. from April 2012 to July 2014. She served as the Chief Consumer Officer of Mars Chocolate North America from November 2009 to March 2012. She served as the Chief Health and Wellbeing Officer at Mars, Incorporated from July 2014 to July 2015. She served as General Manager for McNeil Nutritionals' North American business and was responsible for all aspects of Marketing, Sales, Operations, Communications and Quality Assurance in the United States, Canada, Puerto Rico and the Caribbean. She was responsible for the highly successful consumer launch of SPLENDA® in the U.S. She also developed the ingredient marketing strategies, working with existing and potential new customers for the ingredient brand and developed the global business strategies to drive both the consumer and ingredient product lines in core markets. She began her career at PepsiCo Inc., where she served for 13 years in a variety of marketing positions of increasing responsibility. Among the positions she served as Director of Brand Pepsi and Vice President of Marketing for the Caribbean and Latin American Division of Tricon Restaurants International (Taco Bell, Kentucky Fried Chicken and Pizza Hut). Prior to joining Mars, she spent 10 years with Johnson & Johnson in a variety of leadership roles. She joined the Johnson & Johnson organization in 1999 as Vice President of Worldwide Marketing for McNeil Specialty Products Company. She moved to the Personal Products Company of Johnson & Johnson as Vice President of Worldwide Marketing. In 2002, she returned to McNeil Nutritionals as Worldwide Group Vice President, Marketing. She has been an Independent Director of Gannett Co., Inc. since June 29, 2015. She has been an Independent Director of Archer-Daniels-Midland Company (ADM) since May 5, 2016. She serves as a Director of The Philadelphia Orchestra Association. She has been a Trustee of Hofstra University since July 2008. She serves as a Trustee of Hampton University, The Ad Council, LEAD and the Executive Leadership Council. She has been recognized by Advertising Age as part of the "Power 50 Marketers Award for Excellence in Marketing" (2004), by Ebony magazine as one of the "Top 15 African American Female Executives in Corporate America", by The Network Journal as one of the "Top 25 Influential Black Women in Business" and by Black Enterprise as one of the "Most Powerful African Americans in Corporate America." She has also been named one of the "Outstanding Women in Marketing & Communications." She is the recipient of the 2005 Distinguished Alumna Award from AHBBS, the Association of Hispanic and Black Business Students, an NYU Stern MBA student organization. Click here to read her acceptance speech. Ms. Sandler holds a BBA in International Trade from Hofstra University and an MBA from the Stern School of Business at New York University.Read Full Background




